The samples collected by A.B. Babenko and A.A. Semikolennykh originated from the most favorite sites of the archipelago with the greatest floristic diversity and the richest vegetation, namely, the Tikhaya Bay and Cape Flora (

; 

). Both sampling plots were situated on nearly south-faced slopes under the bird colonies enriching the underlying soils. Because the vegetation of these slopes is strongly patched due to a heterogenous nanorelief and a melting water supply from an up-slope glacier (
